Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 65th Weekly Dose of Optimism.
Things are scary out there. We hope everyone reading this is safe and that =
things will soon stabilize. Our promise is to share some optimism with you =
each week. And even in dark times, we intend to keep that promise.
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
The Weekly Dose is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 Plaid [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/fd39cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-d90a796fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
You may know Plaid [ https://substack.com/redirect/fd39cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-=
d90a796fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU ] as the company that easily lets you connect and authorize your bank =
to your favorite finance apps.When that original product dropped back in 20=
13, it was like magic and unleashed a whole wave of fintech innovation =E2=
=80=93 think Venmo, Chime, and SoFi. In the decade since, Plaid has establi=
shed itself as one of the leading fintech infrastructure companies and has =
rolled out a whole suite of products that allow businesses to get the most =
out of their financial data - including payments, identity verification, an=
d credit.
The company also has a particularly unique vantage point on the fintech ind=
ustry. It partners with both cutting-edge startups and legacy incumbents, h=
as experienced the ups and downs of the general macro environment over the =
last few years, and, as a financial data network, has an inside view of wha=
t=E2=80=99s working in fintech today.
Each year, the company publishes its Fintech Spotlight Report [ https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/fd39cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-d90a796fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Q=
ifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. This year=E2=80=99s repo=
rt, titled =E2=80=9CA Focus on Profitability [ https://substack.com/redirec=
t/fd39cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-d90a796fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Zl=
NuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ],=E2=80=9D covers three main topics: improv=
ing profitability, crypto services, and lending. Whether you=E2=80=99re a f=
intech, lender, banker, investor, or just an interested analyst, you=E2=80=
=99ll find valuable insights inside the report, which they are making free =
to download [ https://substack.com/redirect/fd39cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-d90a796=
fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =
for all Not Boring readers.
(1) A Venture Approach to Peace [ https://substack.com/redirect/49e7f5c9-65=
12-418d-b3ae-175ed49c7853?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
By Dror Poleg
Stable peace hinges on increased trade, investment, and positive-sum intera=
ction among all people in the region=E2=80=94Arabs, Israelis, Muslims, Jews=
, and Christians. When life gets better, and the future seems bright, peopl=
e are less likely to pick up a weapon. When people do business together, th=
ey are less likely to believe hateful lies about their neighbors.
There=E2=80=99s a lot going on in the world right now. Things are quite fra=
gile. It=E2=80=99s a particularly challenging time to remain optimistic abo=
ut the future. Peace in the Middle East seems to be particularly a out of t=
he money bet. Traditional means of diplomacy and peacebuilding don=E2=80=99=
t seem like they=E2=80=99ve gotten us very far.
We, of course, don=E2=80=99t have the answer here.=20
But our friend, Dror Poleg, is working on an interesting idea that, at scal=
e, could be an alternative path towards peace. The basic premise of his pla=
n is that stable peace hinges on increased trade, investment, and positive-=
sum interaction among people in the Middle East.=20
To bring that premise to life, he=E2=80=99s launching a fellowship called T=
he Old New Fellowship, which will bring together entrepreneurs and thinkers=
 working to increase and facilitate investment, trade, and understanding be=
tween people in the region, both Muslims and Jews. Old New will also give g=
rants to the most promising people. The program is modeled off of Tyler Cow=
en=E2=80=99s Emergent Ventures, which supports "entrepreneurs and brilliant=
 minds with highly scalable, 'zero to one' ideas for meaningfully improving=
 society."
You can learn more details about the program here [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/49e7f5c9-6512-418d-b3ae-175ed49c7853?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=20
I (Packy) have had the pleasure of working with, reading, and being friends=
 with Dror for the better part of a decade, and he=E2=80=99s always impress=
ed me with his insight, calm, and ability to stay above the fray and see th=
ings as they really are.
We don=E2=80=99t think Dror would contend this program alone can solve all =
conflict in the Middle East, but we think it=E2=80=99s an important first s=
tep and encourage anyone in the region who has ideas they want to put into =
practice to apply.=20
(2) The Techno-Optimist Manifesto [ https://substack.com/redirect/e4f2f6b9-=
3419-453a-aa06-b29caeedbd30?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Marc Andreessen for a16z
We believe we should place intelligence and energy in a positive feedback l=
oop, and drive them both to infinity.=20
We believe we should use the feedback loop of intelligence and energy to ma=
ke everything we want and need abundant.
Packy here. If you're a regular reader of The Weekly Dose of Optimism, you'=
ve likely already read Marc Andreessen=E2=80=99s recent masterpiece, =E2=80=
=9CThe Techno-Optimist Manifesto.=E2=80=9D I cited it in Riskophilia [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/ef93a25d-2a9e-45ff-9ceb-30589d61e27c?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
OXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] on Tuesday. If you=
 haven=E2=80=99t, stop reading and go read it now.=20
Marc=E2=80=99s manifesto is fiery and has predictably generated a lot of pu=
shback, some cartoonish (looking at you, TechCrunch [ https://substack.com/=
redirect/49605053-8002-43f9-a4a5-25e75a2ef1de?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]) and some thoughtful and nuanced, l=
ike this markup [ https://substack.com/redirect/ff1ce97e-a696-474f-b271-9f6=
ca6ae4f21?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ] from Ben Reinhardt [ https://substack.com/redirect/75c3fa3a-73b7-4206-b=
003-53d878318c14?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m=
8ExkRNpU ] and this thread from Stewart Brand [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/3934dae4-ca37-4aed-9efa-a93ccd47a240?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
Me? I just love it.=20
I know that=E2=80=99s not a particularly critical take. And there are piece=
s of it that not everyone will agree with. I think if the piece were titled=
, =E2=80=9CA Study of the Pros and Cons of Techno-Capitalism and Alternativ=
e Approaches,=E2=80=9D it would be a little one-sided. But it was a manifes=
to, and the point of a manifesto is to serve as a rallying cry. They=E2=80=
=99re supposed to be extreme. They=E2=80=99re supposed to make people think=
=2E=20
This section got people especially riled up:=20
That=E2=80=99s a lot of sacred cows! But the fact is, the mainstream conver=
sation has taken those things as unquestioned and unquestionable Good Thing=
s. At the very least, they should be able to be questioned. Sustainability =
is a good goal=E2=80=A6 but at what human cost? Existential risk is a fine =
thing for people to think about and plan against=E2=80=A6 but not at the ex=
pense of progress. The Precautionary Principle is dangerously one-sided, as=
 I wrote about Tuesday. People in tech should obviously be ethical, but the=
 =E2=80=9Ctech ethics=E2=80=9D push is also part of a broader cultural tren=
d that focuses too much on the potential negatives or limitations of techno=
logical advancements, rather than celebrating their possibilities for progr=
ess and human betterment.=20
De-growth and the limits of growth=E2=80=A6 are just plain ass-backwards. T=
hey don=E2=80=99t work. And any ideology that is willing to trade human lif=
e, health, happiness, and flourishing for anything deserves scrutiny. And u=
pon any serious scrutiny, de-growth and the limits to growth =E2=80=94 a 19=
72 report from the Club of Rome [ https://substack.com/redirect/2b3daa57-a5=
1c-4056-8942-2b9fce19fa50?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=94 fall apart.=20
I believe that humans are good, actually, and that we can collectively make=
 our lives better. I=E2=80=99m glad that Marc wrote something for those of =
us who share that belief to rally around.=20
For a thorough (if one-sided) and data-driven analysis of many of the above=
 points, I highly recommend Johan Norberg=E2=80=99s The Capitalist Manifest=
o [ https://substack.com/redirect/45bba263-b247-40ca-9474-c7b6be4973ca?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], which I s=
tarted reading after seeing John Carmack tweet about it [ https://substack.=
com/redirect/87c00aa4-527f-4d66-935f-70ab392ca7b0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb=
8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. (Marc lists Norberg in his lis=
t of Patron Saints of Techno-Optimism). I=E2=80=99m a card-carrying techno-=
capitalist and techno-optimist, and even I was surprised by a lot of the pr=
o-capitalist arguments he made.
(Disclosure: I am an advisor at a16z crypto, but I think you know me well e=
nough at this point to know that we=E2=80=99re covering this because it=E2=
=80=99s something I believe in.)
(3) How to Scale Nuclear Power [ https://substack.com/redirect/aac956a5-5dc=
6-4b8b-ab2c-36dae74fdb7a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Ryan McEntush for a16z
We need to be mass manufacturing nuclear power plants on the scale of hundr=
eds of gigawatts. The best time to build a vast, civil nuclear fleet was 50=
 years ago. The second best time is now.
OK, we=E2=80=99re sorry for the a16z love, but those guys were on fire this=
 week. Ryan McEntush, an American Dynamism investor at a16z, published a su=
per thorough, but digestible primer on the history and future of nuclear en=
ergy. If Andreessen thinks we =E2=80=9Cshould place intelligence and energy=
 in a positive feedback loop, and drive them both to infinity,=E2=80=9D nuc=
lear energy will most likely have to play a big role in that.=20
McEntush=E2=80=99s essay does a strong job explaining how we ended up with =
the current state of affairs in nuclear =E2=80=94 unfounded safety concerns=
, regulation, special interests, etc. Thankfully, he sees that progress is =
unfolding as the =E2=80=9Ctides are turning=E2=80=9D with the public=E2=80=
=99s perception of nuclear and startups race to work around both regulatory=
 and economic barriers of nuclear progression.
Of course, this is a particular area of interest here at Not Boring. Next w=
eek Packy is launching a new podcast called Age of Miracles [ https://subst=
ack.com/redirect/dd350d22-33f4-4bda-bfc8-27ff3321e79f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qif=
Q.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=94 it=E2=80=99s a po=
dcast about the industries helping to create a world of superabundance and =
Season 1 is all about nuclear.=20
(4) Figure 01 [ https://substack.com/redirect/3abbefb5-d0c1-4ae8-bfca-2cd0a=
ae33207?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
]
We=E2=80=99re going to need a lot of energy if we=E2=80=99re going to elect=
rify our workforce.
In a development sure to send shivers down the spines of techno-optimism=E2=
=80=99s enemies, Figure released a bipedal humanoid robot this week (just 1=
2 months after the company was started=E2=80=A6).
It=E2=80=99s an important =E2=80=A6 step =E2=80=A6 towards the company=E2=
=80=99s stated goal to =E2=80=9Cdevelop general purpose humanoids that make=
 a positive impact on humanity and create a better life for future generati=
ons. These robots can eliminate the need for unsafe and undesirable jobs =
=E2=80=94 ultimately allowing us to live happier, more purposeful lives.=E2=
=80=9D=20
Now to some, that=E2=80=99s a pretty scary proposition. If Figure and compe=
titors like Tesla Bot are successful, they could eliminate millions of jobs=
=2E The human mind is really good at fo=
recasting out that downside case: mill=
ions of lost jobs =3D bad. And to be fair, it kind of looks like Terminator=
=2E
The human mind is less good at forecasting out the upside case: millions of=
 undesirable jobs filled by robots, freeing up humans to focus their time a=
nd energy on higher-level pursuits. What those will be is harder to predict=
 and so we tend to focus more on the downside, knowable scenario.=20
Plus, as Packy wrote about in his piece on Formic [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/84250de8-ad7b-40f0-a80d-b395de8960e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], the fear of lost jobs from automatio=
n is overblown. Factories face a labor shortage that robots can help fill, =
and cheaper robot labor means cheaper things, lower inflation, and ultimate=
ly, abundance.
We=E2=80=99re rooting for Figure and that upside case.
(5) Direct File [ https://substack.com/redirect/fc032fd9-0347-47c5-9ffb-d95=
d7a3f3044?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U ]
From the IRS
As directed by the Treasury Department, the IRS is taking steps to implemen=
t a limited Direct File pilot for the 2024 filing season to further assess =
customer support and technology needs and address solutions for issues iden=
tified in the report the IRS submitted to Congress earlier this year.
The Direct File pilot will provide eligible taxpayers with the choice to el=
ectronically file their 2023 federal tax return for free, directly with the=
 IRS.
This is probably the first and last time you=E2=80=99ll hear us cheering fo=
r IRS-built software in the Weekly Dose, but Intuit had it coming.=20
The company has engaged in a 20-year lobbying effort [ https://substack.com=
/redirect/e2150be6-ccd7-4f0c-96b2-ddb3b022abbd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5=
T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] to prevent the US from doing what =
other advanced countries have done: make tax filing free and simple for its=
 citizens. Tax season isn=E2=80=99t fun =E2=80=94 giving away a quarter to =
a half of your hard-earned money is the least fun thing imaginable =E2=80=
=94 but Intuit has poured its significant resources into making it even les=
s fun. Our favorite is the company=E2=80=99s efforts to stop a ReturnFree T=
ax System =E2=80=94 pre-filing with the information the government already =
has. As it stands, we have to tell the IRS how much we owe, and they either=
 say =E2=80=9COK, cool, that=E2=80=99s right=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CNo that=
=E2=80=99s not how much you owe, you=E2=80=99re in trouble now.=E2=80=9D If=
 they knew the whole time, why tf do we have to go through all that headach=
e? Intuit, mainly. =20
It=E2=80=99s exactly the kind of regulatory capture that Bill Gurley railed=
 against [ https://substack.com/redirect/fda57dc0-1560-4958-9217-f791f843c2=
3a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], an=
d the fact that Intuit was able to wield it not against startups, but again=
st the government itself, shows how powerful that revolving door can be.=20
Well, we have goos news: that reign of terror has ended. Starting in 2024 (=
ie when we pay our 2023 taxes), residents in 13 states will be able to use =
Direct File, the IRS=E2=80=99 free electronic tax filing pilot program. Thi=
s is a big win for regular folk who no longer have to pay extra for the ple=
asure of paying the government taxes. That racket seems to be coming to a c=
lose with the rollout of Direct File next year.=20
There=E2=80=99s work to be done. All 50 states should get to experience thi=
s bliss. The government still needs to prove it can build something better =
than healthcare.gov. We want to see a ReturnFree Tax System.=20
But for now, paying taxes might just get a little bit less miserable.
That=E2=80=99s all for this week. If you have some time this weekend, check=
 out Plaid=E2=80=99s Fintech Spotlight. [ https://substack.com/redirect/fd3=
9cd9a-8ace-4763-acf8-d90a796fc8e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZ=
jmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
We=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox on Tuesday.
Thanks for reading,
Dan + Packy

