ory and future of nuclear energy. If Andreessen thinks we &#8220;should pla=
ce intelligence and energy in a positive feedback loop, and drive them both=
 to infinity,&#8221; nuclear energy will most likely have to play a big rol=
e in that. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">McEntush&#8217;s essay does a strong job e=
xplaining how we ended up with the current state of affairs in nuclear &#82=
12; unfounded safety concerns, regulation, special interests, etc. Thankful=
ly, he sees that progress is unfolding as the &#8220;tides are turning&#822=
1; with the public&#8217;s perception of nuclear and startups race to work =
around both regulatory and economic barriers of nuclear progression.</p><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Of course, this is a particular area of interest here =
