12; ultimately allowing us to live happier, more purposeful lives.&#8221; <=
/em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Now to some, that&#8217;s a pretty scary proposit=
ion. If Figure and competitors like Tesla Bot are successful, they could el=
iminate millions of jobs. The human mind is really good at forecasting out =
that downside case: millions of lost jobs =3D bad. And to be fair, it kind =
of looks like Terminator.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The human mind is less good =
at forecasting out the upside case: millions of undesirable jobs filled by =
robots, freeing up humans to focus their time and energy on higher-level pu=
rsuits. What those will be is harder to predict and so we tend to focus mor=
e on the downside, knowable scenario. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Plus, as =
Packy wrote about in </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/84250d=
e8-ad7b-40f0-a80d-b395de8960e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjml=
XXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoratio=
n: underline;">his piece on Formic</a><span>, the fear of lost jobs from au=
tomation is overblown. Factories face a labor shortage that robots can help=
 fill, and cheaper robot labor means cheaper things, lower inflation, and u=
ltimately, abundance.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217;re rooting for F=
igure and that upside case.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>(5)</strong><span>=
