-9ffb-d95d7a3f3044?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline=
;">Direct File</a></strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>From the IRS</em></p><=
blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding=
: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>As directed by the Treasury =
Department, the IRS is taking steps to implement a limited Direct File pilo=
t for the 2024 filing season to further assess customer support and technol=
ogy needs and address solutions for issues identified in the report the IRS=
 submitted to Congress earlier this year.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64=
, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-l=
eft: 20px;"><em>The Direct File pilot will provide eligible taxpayers with =
the choice to electronically file their 2023 federal tax return for free, d=
irectly with the IRS.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This is probab=
ly the first and last time you&#8217;ll hear us cheering for IRS-built soft=
ware in the Weekly Dose, but Intuit had it coming. </p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><s=
pan>The company has engaged in a </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/e2150be6-ccd7-4f0c-96b2-ddb3b022abbd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); te=
xt-decoration: underline;">20-year lobbying effort</a><span> to prevent the=
 US from doing what other advanced countries have done: make tax filing fre=
e and simple for its citizens. Tax season isn&#8217;t fun &#8212; giving aw=
ay a quarter to a half of your hard-earned money is the least fun thing ima=
ginable &#8212; but Intuit has poured its significant resources into making=
 it even less fun. Our favorite is the company&#8217;s efforts to stop a Re=
turnFree Tax System &#8212; pre-filing with the information the government =
already has. As it stands, we have to tell the IRS how much we owe, and the=
y either say &#8220;OK, cool, that&#8217;s right&#8221; or &#8220;No that&#=
8217;s not how much you owe, you&#8217;re in trouble now.&#8221; If they kn=
ew the whole time, why tf do we have to go through all that headache? Intui=
t, mainly.  </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It&#8217;s exactly the kind =
of regulatory capture that </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/=
fda57dc0-1560-4958-9217-f791f843c23a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-dec=
oration: underline;">Bill Gurley railed against</a><span>, and the fact tha=
t Intuit was able to wield it not against startups, but against the governm=
ent itself, shows how powerful that revolving door can be. </span></p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">Well, we have goos news: that reign of terror has ended. Start=
ing in 2024 (ie when we pay our 2023 taxes), residents in 13 states will be=
 able to use Direct File, the IRS&#8217; free electronic tax filing pilot p=
rogram. This is a big win for regular folk who no longer have to pay extra =
for the pleasure of paying the government taxes. That racket seems to be co=
ming to a close with the rollout of Direct File next year. </p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">There&#8217;s work to be done. All 50 states should get to experience=
 this bliss. The government still needs to prove it can build something bet=
ter than healthcare.gov. We want to see a ReturnFree Tax System. </p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">But for now, paying taxes might just get a little bit less mise=
rable.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"b=
ackground: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"=
